issues.description: The problem statement explicitly requires the attribute 'rides' in ExcellenceLand to be private (and of type List<Ride>), but the solution implementation declares this field as public (public List<Ride> rides). This contradicts the stated visibility in the exercise text and may confuse students (or cause automated checks) about the required encapsulation and the need for a private field plus a public getter.
issues.suggested_fix: Make the 'rides' attribute private in the implementation to match the problem statement (private List<Ride> rides), keep or provide a public getter getRides(), and ensure the constructor assigns to this private field. Update the template/solution accordingly so students see the intended encapsulation.
